[pause]
[draws on board] Let me give this a slightly

00:16:19.079 --> 00:16:28.769
nicer rounded thing. What happens with all
businesses is that they go through seven stages,

00:16:28.769 --> 00:16:36.180
four of which indicated by these wiggly lines,
are clearly points of difficulty. And three

00:16:36.180 --> 00:16:43.680
of which indicated by these rather straighter
lines are theoretically smooth, more smooth

00:16:43.680 --> 00:16:50.420
running. In fact, one of the last difficult
areas is a trap, we'll see that, why that

00:16:50.420 --> 00:16:56.320
is in just a moment or two. But essentially
what happens is that every business, every

00:16:56.320 --> 00:17:03.220
organization, every group that's trying to
get started goes through initially a stage

00:17:03.220 --> 00:17:10.869
that I call 'early struggle'. Pretty self
evident that any organization would go through

00:17:10.869 --> 00:17:15.199
a stage of early struggle. In business terms,
what do you think the struggle is about? What's

00:17:15.199 --> 00:17:17.539
the struggle for? Yeah.
