a 'synergist'. It's not a great word but it's

00:40:32.370 --> 00:40:37.710
the best one I can think of. And essentially
what a synergist management style is is a

00:40:37.710 --> 00:40:44.330
realization that we have to have systems and
processes for the long term but they've gotta

00:40:44.330 --> 00:40:50.960
work with the people in our organization and
with our culture. It's the synergist mindset

00:40:50.960 --> 00:40:56.550
that translates for these people that smooths
the way, that enables them to talk to each

00:40:56.550 --> 00:41:02.160
other. And it's that synergist mindset that
appear when we get all four of these working

00:41:02.160 --> 00:41:08.260
together that the organization can stay in
predictable success. And it's when one of

00:41:08.260 --> 00:41:14.740
those begins to feel under pressure and leaves,
or gets pushed down that the organization

00:41:14.740 --> 00:41:19.360
comes unbalanced and will either fall backwards
into whitewater or forward into treadmill.

