look at your hiring and make sure. 'Cause
hiring is really the water coming into the

00:49:58.840 --> 00:50:03.370
lake. Right? It's the only thing that's gonna
refresh what's there. Secondly the way in

00:50:03.370 --> 00:50:08.450
which you conduct performance assessment.
Typically in treadmill, performance assessments

00:50:08.450 --> 00:50:16.490
begin to become risk and consequence focused.
'What did you not do?' 'What did you fail

00:50:16.490 --> 00:50:20.960
on?' And 'what were the consequences of that?'
as opposed to being focused on 'What did you

00:50:20.960 --> 00:50:25.070
do really well? What did you succeed at? And
how can we bottle that in the organization?

00:50:25.070 --> 00:50:32.000
How can we push that out to wider parts of
the business?' And the two other things are

00:50:32.000 --> 00:50:37.040
the training function. Classically in treadmill,
training has again begun to move towards a

00:50:37.040 --> 00:50:43.190
compliance base. It's begun to become a way
in which you insure that all the boxes are

00:50:43.190 --> 00:50:47.240
ticked and we're covered. Our people have
got, been touched at all these points and

00:50:47.240 --> 00:50:51.030
they know what they should know. And to turn
the training function into something that

00:50:51.030 --> 00:50:58.910
encourages creativity. All the good stuff
that you're doin'. That's three. And mentoring

00:50:58.910 --> 00:51:05.220
and coaching. One of the key things in treadmill
is you've gotta give people an opportunity

00:51:05.220 --> 00:51:10.820
to do things wrong. It's like a golfer whose
swing's gone bad. There's no point trying

00:51:10.820 --> 00:51:15.720
to get him to fix it on the back nine on Sunday.
You gotta get him off to the range and let

00:51:15.720 --> 00:51:20.400
him hit a hundred balls and keep trying stuff
until they get the groove back. And mentoring

00:51:20.400 --> 00:51:25.550
and coaching that takes people off line and
lets them make mistakes is very, very important.

